snippet: The Department of Health and Human Services said fewer than 10 million people would have coverage purchased through insurance exchanges by the end of 2015.
abstract: Health Sec Sylvia Mathews Burwell offers surprisingly modest estimate of number of people who will sign up for health insurance in second round of open enrollment; says 9.1 million people will have such coverage at end of 2015.
lead_paragraph: The Department of Health and Human Services said fewer than 10 million people would have coverage purchased through insurance exchanges by the end of 2015.
